title: $3,000 Razer #PC can't be fixed! Razer WORSE than Apple w/ Right to Repair #tech #technology #shorts
description: This is the second time I've been stopped from repairing a 2022 Razer Blade 15 Advanced computer because of lack of replacement parts. Razer is worse than Apple when it comes to right to repair because they outright refuse to sell replacement parts for any of their technology . At least Apple will sell you overpriced replacement parts that cost more than your device is worth. My customer is stuck with a pc that has a broken 4K OLED Display that uses proprietary tech , so they will have to send it in to Razer and pay over $600 to get it fixed. This is why I say the computer repair industry is dying. It's not like I'm trying to fix a CPU or GPU in my computer repair shop, I'm just trying to replace a broken display. Crazy.

title: 30 year old IBM ThinkPad puts modern #tech to shame #pc #technology #shorts
description: This 30 year old IBM ThinkPad shows how important build quality is when it comes to making a laptop last. Back in 1994 this thick piece of technology cost $4500 which is $9500 in today's money, but what you got was a computer that could physically hold up after 30 years. Of course the tech is obsolete now, but this pc proves how long they can last if the company isn't afraid to innovate and they don't cut corners with the design. Imagine having this build quality in a modern gaming laptop? Not to mention the ability to upgrade everything because it's modular. But anyways, here's some more RGB.

title: They fixed the reason my phone broke! #CES2024
Japan Just Unlocked GOD MODE Internet - 125,000,000 Mbps #shorts
description:
Japan has recently set a new world record in internet speed by reaching an incredible 1.02 petabits per second. To put it simply, this speed is so fast that you could download over 125,000 gigabytes of data in just one second. It‚Äôs millions of times faster than the internet most people use today.

The breakthrough was made using a special kind of fiber optic cable that has 19 separate cores. These cores allow data to travel in multiple streams at the same time, much like a superhighway with 19 lanes. Even though it‚Äôs much more powerful, the cable is the same size as regular fiber lines, making it easier to use with existing technology.

The team tested this high-speed connection over a long distance‚Äîmore than 1,800 kilometers‚Äîwithout losing speed or quality. This means it could be useful for long-range data transfer, such as across countries or under the ocean.

While this ultra-fast internet isn‚Äôt available to the public yet, it shows what might be possible in the near future. It could play a big role in future technologies like 6G, global cloud services, and AI systems that need to move massive amounts of data instantly.

title: Technology in Assetto Corsa EVO
description:
What makes a circuit feel truly real?
The same Laserscan technology that defined Assetto Corsa and Assetto Corsa Competizione lies at the heart of Assetto Corsa EVO. It captures every kerb, camber, and surface imperfection with millimetric precision.

Combined with Lidar, Photo Scan, and the expert hands of our artists, each track is sculpted in detail, right down to the rumble strips and wheel feedback. All of it comes to life through the KUNOS physics engine and reaches your hands via Force Feedback.

Visual fidelity is strongly supported by volumetric global illumination, high definition modeling and environmental sounds.

In version AC EVO 0.3, you‚Äôll feel it on two new legendary circuits:
Spa-Francorchamps and Red Bull Ring.
